From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Julien Jerphanion <git@jjerphan.xyz>
Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 11/11] Add ppc64le to python/dist ABI suffix map

Bazel's TARGET_CPU for linux-ppc64le builds is "ppc64le", but patch 0005
only mapped "ppc". Without this entry, py_dist_module fails during analysis
with: key "ppc64le" not found in dictionary.
---
 python/dist/dist.bzl | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/python/dist/dist.bzl b/python/dist/dist.bzl
index 4034e7c9a..a8f3c2d1b 100644
--- a/python/dist/dist.bzl
+++ b/python/dist/dist.bzl
@@ -29,6 +29,7 @@ def _get_suffix(limited_api, python_version, cpu):
             "linux-aarch_64": "aarch64-linux-gnu",
             "aarch64": "aarch64-linux-gnu",
             "ppc": "powerpc64le-linux-gnu",
+            "ppc64le": "powerpc64le-linux-gnu",
             "linux-x86_64": "x86_64-linux-gnu",
             "k8": "x86_64-linux-gnu",
             "s390x": "s390x-linux-gnu",
